text: Russian President Vladimir Putin, speaking at a press conference in Moscow, said that for a "long-term settlement" of the conflict between Ukraine and Russia, Ukraine must recognize Russia's annexation of Crimea, refuse to join NATO and, as Putin put it, demilitarize. Putin also said that Russia recognized the so-called "DNR" and "LNR" within the borders of the Donetsk and Lugansk regions of Ukraine. At the same time, most of these areas are now under the control of the Ukrainian authorities, and not separatists. ‚ÄúAs for the borders, within what borders will we recognize these republics. We recognized them, which means that we recognized all their fundamental documents, including the Constitution. the time when they were part of Ukraine. But we expect that all contentious issues will be resolved during negotiations between the Kiev authorities and the leadership of the republics," Putin said.
